  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220ºC/ 200ºC (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Pick a few<strong> coriander leaves</strong> and set them aside for garnish, then chop the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> ginger</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1698141348579-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1698141348579-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1698141348579-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1698141348579-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1698141348579-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the<strong> red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>,<strong> ginger</strong> and<strong> chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and grind to a paste</p><p>Tip: If you don't have a pestle and mortar, chop everything very finely!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1698141352858-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1698141352858-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1698141352858-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1698141352858-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1698141352858-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong>, the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and mix to combine – this is your <strong>spicy green chutney</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skin on) into large bite-sized pieces</p><p>Cut your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> into quarters, leaving the skins and root on (this stops them drying out and falling apart when roasting)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1698141360201-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1698141360201-x400.jpg",
